Most people run & hide...Pretend to not see or hear...It's almost as if they become blind & deaf to their surroundings. Why? I guess because they see it as an annoyance. Or "they don't have enough time"..or most likely they've already judged the other person before they've even had a chance to speak. I have no room to judge, because I've even done it before. "Don't make eye contact, don't make eye contact, just don't make eye contact". Lol. But God changed my heart & since then...I'm not gonna lie..Whenever someone asks me "can you help me out" or "can you spare me some change?" I give it to them.. Naive? Crazy? Dumb? Not smart? Think whatever you want to think. I'll do what I want to do. Because the way I see it, it's an opportunity to sow into someone's life. It's an opportunity not only to say I'm a Christian, but to show I'm a Christian. To not only preach with my words, but with my actions--my life.. To not just say it, but to live it. Most of these people just want someone to acknowledge that they exist. That they're valuable.They want to be treated like they're human..not some kinda "scum" of the earth. How many times have you walked by &  judged them before you even got their name? "All they do is beg." "They probably got more money than me", "they're gonna go spend it on..blah..blah..blah" SHUT UP! Lol. Until you've actually taken the time to talk to them & get to know them & their story---Don't talk to me.. A life is a life. All I'm saying is, if they matter to Jesus..They better matter to you too. We hear the "good samaritan" story all the time & think "what such jerks" about the priests that walked on by someone in need, when we do it everyday. Lol. You want to reach the world? But I just want to challenge you, the next time someone asks you for money..don't judge them..talk to them first.. Most people run & hide...Pretend to not see or hear...It's almost as if they become blind & deaf to their surroundings. Why? I guess because they see it as an annoyance. Or "they don't have enough time"..or most likely they've already judged the other person before they've even had a chance to speak. I have no room to judge, because I've even done it before. "Don't make eye contact, don't make eye contact, just don't make eye contact". Lol. But God changed my heart & since then...I'm not gonna lie..Whenever someone asks me "can you help me out" or "can you spare me some change?" I give it to them.. Naive? Crazy? Dumb? Not smart? Think whatever you want to think. I'll do what I want to do. Because the way I see it, it's an opportunity to sow into someone's life. It's an opportunity not only to say I'm a Christian, but to show I'm a Christian. To not only preach with my words, but with my actions--my life.. To not just say it, but to live it. Most of these people just want someone to acknowledge that they exist. That they're valuable.They want to be treated like they're human..not some kinda "scum" of the earth. How many times have you walked by &  judged them before you even got their name? "All they do is beg." "They probably got more money than me", "they're gonna go spend it on..blah..blah..blah" SHUT UP! Lol. Until you've actually taken the time to talk to them & get to know them & their story---Don't talk to me.. A life is a life. All I'm saying is, if they matter to Jesus..They better matter to you too. We hear the "good samaritan" story all the time & think "what such jerks" about the priests that walked on by someone in need, when we do it everyday. Lol. You want to reach the world? How can you if you can't even reach the people in you own backyard. I'm not "ranting" ok maybe I am.. Lol. But I just want to challenge you, the next time someone asks you for money..don't judge them..talk to them first.. Your life & your perspective will be forever changed. #lifeofpipes #missions #homeless #tiptoe #friends #strangers #random #thestreets #theloop #delmarloop #Jesus #walkthewalk #missions #dontjudge #openyoureyes #harmonica #light #happa

Most people run & hide...Pretend to not see or hear...It's almost as if they become blind & deaf to their surroundings. Why? I guess because they see it as an annoyance. Or "they don't have enough time"..or most likely they've already judged the other person before they've even had a chance to speak. I have no room to judge, because I've even done it before. "Don't make eye contact, don't make eye contact, just don't make eye contact". Lol. But God changed my heart & since then...I'm not gonna lie..Whenever someone asks me "can you help me out" or "can you spare me some change?" I give it to them.. Naive? Crazy? Dumb? Not smart? Think whatever you want to think. I'll do what I want to do. Because the way I see it, it's an opportunity to sow into someone's life. It's an opportunity not only to say I'm a Christian, but to show I'm a Christian. To not only preach with my words, but with my actions--my life.. To not just say it, but to live it. Most of these people just want someone to acknowledge that they exist. That they're valuable.They want to be treated like they're human..not some kinda "scum" of the earth. How many times have you walked by &  judged them before you even got their name? "All they do is beg." "They probably got more money than me", "they're gonna go spend it on..blah..blah..blah" SHUT UP! Lol. Until you've actually taken the time to talk to them & get to know them & their story---Don't talk to me.. A life is a life. All I'm saying is, if they matter to Jesus..They better matter to you too. We hear the "good samaritan" story all the time & think "what such jerks" about the priests that walked on by someone in need, when we do it everyday. Lol. You want to reach the world? How can you if you can't even reach the people in you own backyard. I'm not "ranting" ok maybe I am.. Lol. But I just want to challenge you, the next time someone asks you for money..don't judge them..talk to them first.. Your life & your perspective will be forever changed. #lifeofpipes #missions #homeless #tiptoe #friends #strangers #random #thestreets #theloop #delmarloop #Jesus #walkthewalk #missions #dontjudge #openyoureyes #harmonica #light #happa
